"title": "5778: adorning",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5778",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A form of ornamentation, using especially jewels and precious metals, to enhance the beauty of buildings or people.</p>\n<h2>Buildings were adorned with various materials</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr3:6\">2CH 3:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:8\">PSA 45:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa60:13\">ISA 60:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos3:15\">AMO 3:15</a></p>\n<h2>Objects of worship were adorned</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos10:1\">HOS 10:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:3-Jer10:4\">JER 10:3–10:4</a></p>\n<h2>Women adorned themselves with jewellery and fine clothes</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:11-Ezek16:12\">EZK 16:11–16:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:24\">2SA 1:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:30\">JER 4:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:13\">EZK 16:13</a></p>\n<h2>Personal adornment should not be allowed to detract from worship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:9\">1TI 2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:3-1Pet3:4\">1PE 3:3–3:4</a></p>\n<h2>Adorning used in a metaphorical sense</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:10\">ISA 61:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job40:10\">JOB 40:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps93:5\">PSA 93:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps144:12\">PSA 144:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:8-Prov1:9\">PRO 1:8–1:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa60:7\">ISA 60:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:2\">REV 21:2</a></p>",
